# Defence-in-depth exclusions for `npm pack` and `npm publish` from the repo
# root. The canonical release pipeline runs `npm run build:release-archive`
# first to stage a transformed copy of the repository under `.release-staging/`
# (T-V05-013, ADR-0021, SPEC-V05-010), then packs from that staging dir — so
# this file is the secondary safety net for an operator who packs the repo
# directly without staging.
#
# `package.json#files` is the primary include allowlist. Anything not listed
# there is already excluded by npm. The patterns below cover paths that COULD
# end up in a packed archive if the `files` field were broadened by accident
# or if a maintainer ran `npm pack` outside the release pipeline.
#
# When changing this file, also update:
# - `package.json#files` (the canonical include list).
# - `scripts/lib/release-archive-builder.ts` (build-time filter that produces
#   the staged tree).
# - `docs/release-package-contents.md` (the contract documentation).
# - `tools/automation-registry.yml` (the automation inventory).

# Numbered ADRs ship in the codebase only — the consumer's first ADR is
# their own ADR-0001, not a continuation of ours (ADR-0021 §Decision.2,
# SPEC-V05-010 assertion 1).
docs/adr/[0-9][0-9][0-9][0-9]-*.md

# Local maintainer state — never relevant to consumers.
.worktrees/

# Build-time staging directory produced by `npm run build:release-archive`.
# Excluded so that staging output cannot recursively land inside a packed
# archive when the release pipeline is rerun against a dirty checkout.
.release-staging/
